# Gubbins environment configuration — copy to `.env` and fill in.
#
# `.env` and `.env.*` are git-ignored; this `.env.example` (placeholders only) is the
# single tracked template. NEVER put a real secret in a tracked file.

# ─── Google Drive cloud sync (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# The PUBLIC OAuth 2.0 client id used for browser-only Google Drive sync. This is not a
# secret (it ships in the client bundle by design); there is NO client secret.
#
# Setup (see docs/dev/google-drive-sync.md for the full walk-through):
#   1. Google Cloud Console → create a project → enable the "Google Drive API".
#   2. Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID of type "Web application".
#   3. Add your app origins to "Authorised JavaScript origins" and the exact app URLs
#      (with the /Gubbins/ base + trailing slash) to "Authorised redirect URIs", e.g.
#        https://YOURNAME.github.io/Gubbins/
#        http://localhost:5173/Gubbins/
#   4. Paste the generated client id below.
#
# Leave unset to hide the Google Drive option (the rest of the app is unaffected).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
